MISCELLANEOUS DISMISSALS

2003-2165. State v. Koliser.

Mahoning C.P. No. 03CR535. This cause is pending before the court as a death penalty appeal from the Court of Common Pleas of Mahoning County. On May 19, 2005, counsel for appellant filed a suggestion of death indicating that appellant is deceased. Accordingly,

IT IS ORDERED by the court, sua sponte, that this cause be, and hereby is, dismissed.
